  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <p><seg type="diplomatic" subtype="address"><seg type="diplomatic" subtype="intitulatio">David king of Scots</seg> to all his worthy men in the shire of Edinburgh, <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="salutation">Greeting</seg>:</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="prohibition">I forbid that anyone should take anything from the land that I have given in
                  alms to the church of Holyrood in Edinburgh, unless by
                  licence and consent of the canons serving God and Holyrood
                  there, that is, neither in grass nor in peats or other
                  things, unless by the consent of the aforesaid canons.</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="witnesses">As witness, John the bishop.</seg> At Edinburgh.</p>
      </div>
    </body>
